			<section id="two" class="wrapper style2 align-center">
				<div class="container">
					<header>
						<a name="rsi"></a>
						<h2>Resource Pack Issues</h2>
						<p>Sometimes, the resource pack will not be downloaded to your client, or wont request you to download it at all. To solve this, simply ensure that your multiplayer settings ALLOW prompt links, and, you have not already denied the request. Once you have ensured the settings are correct, simply connect to a different ulticraft address. For example, if you connect with "play.ulticraft.com" change it to something different, such as "anything.ulticraft.com" or even "literally-anything-you-could-want.ulticraft.com", then, if you have your settings correct, accept the resource pack download, and you are good to go!</p>
						<h2>Step by Step</h2>
						<table>
							<tr><td>1. Disconnect from the server.</td></tr>
							<tr><td>2. From the title screen, click Options > Multiplayer Settings. Ensure prompt on links is ON</td></tr>
							<tr><td>3. Select Ulticraft on your server list, click edit</td></tr>
							<tr><td>4. Change the address to resourcepack.ulticraft.com (or anything.ulticraft.com). This is to get minecraft to re-request it.</td></tr>
							<tr><td>5. Join the server, and accept the resource pack download, then wait a few seconds. Press [CROUCH] + [DROP]. If you see gems, it worked!</td></tr>
						</table>
						<p>Optionally, you can download the resource pack manually: <a href="http://ulticraft.com/resources/internal/resourcepack/latest.zip" class="button alt">Download Resource Pack</a></p>
					</header>
					<header>
						<a name="gems"></a>
						<h2>What are Gems?</h2>
						<p>Gems are what puts the Ultimate in Ulticraft! Gems can be used to unlock perks, upgrade perks, and much more.</p>
						<a href="#getgems" class="button ">How to Get Gems</a> <a href="gems#perks" class="button">View Perks</a>
					</header>
					<header>
						<a name="getgems"></a>
						<h2>How to get Gems?</h2>
						<p>Gems are not earned by selling things or converting from ingame money. Gems are a unique currency to represent your expirience. Gems are earned by literally playing the game, discovering new locations, being online, breaking/placing blocks, killing mobs / enemies. Pretty anything you do in minecraft, will be something you can earn gems on. Even your chat usage can be awarded via gems. If you are looking for lots of gems, or even immortality, you can always help us help you help us! Check out our webstore <a href="store#gems">HERE</a></p>
						<a href="#gems" class="button">What Gems Are</a> <a href="store#gems" class="button">Get Extra Gems</a>
					</header>
